title: Strauss, R. - Metamorphosen, Sonatina No. 1 for winds - Previn,
description:
Richard Strauss' Metamorphosen and Sonatina No. 1 for 16 wind instruments.

Strauss' Metamorphosen and Sonatina No. 1 for wind, recorded by Andre Previn and the Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra and released by Philips in 1987. Although seemingly unsung, Metamorphosen is a masterful work of 20th Century music. It can be heard as a requiem for Germanic culture, which lay in ruins when the piece was written in 1945. Very moving, indeed.

Please enjoy.
